BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:sound-art-lab-sounds-of-the-future-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260722T104007Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20261101
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20261102
SUMMARY:Deadline: Sound Art Lab: Sounds of the Future Residency (Autumn 202
 6 Round)
DESCRIPTION:A funded residency at Sound Art Lab in Struer with a genuine we
 ekly stipend rather than just space. Facilities suit computer-based and au
 diovisual work: a private studio\, professional stereo\, surround and mult
 ichannel recording\, an electronics workshop and a woodworking workshop\, 
 plus a sound equipment depot\, mentoring and technical support. The reside
 ncy also includes promotion through Sound Art Lab's channels. Required mat
 erials are a project description of up to one page\, a CV of up to two pag
 es\, a portfolio of sound work samples of up to ten pages and 20MB total\,
  and your preferred residency dates. Applications go through Koda's online
  system. Two deadlines each year\, 1 May and 1 November\, both 23:59. Run 
 with SPOR festival\, Dansk Komponistforening and Koda Kultur\, funded by K
 oda Kultur and Region Midtjylland's Culture Development Pool.\n\nOrganisat
 ion: Sound Art Lab (with SPOR festival\, Danish Composers' Society / Dansk
  Komponistforening\, and Koda Kultur)\nLocation: Struer\, Denmark. Aimed a
 t artists connected to the Danish sound art scene\; individuals and groups
  both eligible. Applicants must not be currently enrolled in education. Ko
 da membership is not required\, but applications should align with Dansk K
 omponistforening's support criteria. International applicants without NemI
 D are told to contact Koda for login assistance\, so lacking Danish creden
 tials is a friction point rather than a hard disqualification.\nAward: DKK
  10\,000 per week for up to 3 weeks (up to DKK 30\,000)\, covering travel\
 , accommodation\, artist fee\, equipment purchases\, software and consulti
 ng\, plus free accommodation in Sound Art Lab's shared 210 sqm artist apar
 tment and full access to studio facilities. Two residencies are awarded pe
 r deadline. No participation fee\, no co-financing.\nDuration: 3 consecuti
 ve weeks\, to be taken within the 6 months following the deadline\n\nMore:
  https://kultur.koda.dk/legatoversigt/sounds-of-the-future-residency-paa-s
 ound-art-lab/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://kultur.koda.dk/legatoversigt/sounds-of-the-future-residency-paa
 -sound-art-lab/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Struer\, Denmark. Aimed at artists connected to the Danish sound a
 rt scene\; individuals and groups both eligible. Applicants must not be cu
 rrently enrolled in education. Koda membership is not required\, but appli
 cations should align with Dansk Komponistforening's support criteria. Inte
 rnational applicants without NemID are told to contact Koda for login assi
 stance\, so lacking Danish credentials is a friction point rather than a h
 ard disqualification.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:siirtymä-ambient-festival-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260722T104007Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260630
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260701
SUMMARY:Deadline: Siirtymä Ambient Music Festival 2026: Open Call (Tampere
 \, Finland)
DESCRIPTION:Siirtymä Ambient Music Festival 2026 is a free\, community-dri
 ven festival in Tampere\, Finland\, organised by Suomen Ambientyhdistys ry
  (Finnish Ambient Association). The festival uses overlapping simultaneous
  performances across multiple locations\, emphasising spatial and ambient 
 experience over traditional stage formats. Open to artists and collectives
  working in ambient music\, sound art\, spatial installations\, and interd
 isciplinary practices\; no career-stage restriction\; the festival priorit
 ises emerging and lesser-known artists. The 2026 theme focuses on strength
 ening diversity\, creating multiple voices\, and finding new ways to encou
 nter one another and the urban environment. Technical support is provided 
 to selected participants. No travel or accommodation funding is publicly c
 onfirmed. NOTE: deadline of June 30 is from the Community Arts Network PDF
 \; verify at https://siirtyma.com/en/siirtym-2026 before submitting. Conta
 ct Suomen Ambientyhdistys ry directly for application details.\n\nOrganisa
 tion: Suomen Ambientyhdistys ry (Finnish Ambient Association)\nLocation: T
 ampere\, Finland (multiple simultaneous venues\, site-specific)\nAward: Te
 chnical support provided. No artist fee publicly confirmed. No application
  fee.\nDuration: Festival date: 5 September 2026.\n\nMore: https://siirtym
 a.com/en/siirtym-2026?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=ref
 erral
URL:https://siirtyma.com/en/siirtym-2026?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantd
 esk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Tampere\, Finland (multiple simultaneous venues\, site-specific)
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:prohelvetia-creation-production-contemporary-music-2026@artificialnouve
 au.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260722T104007Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260901
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260902
SUMMARY:Deadline: Creation and Production: Contemporary Music
DESCRIPTION:Pro Helvetia's creation and production grant for contemporary m
 usic supports the creation and production of new musical works\, including
  commissioned compositions\, music theatre\, sound installations\, and con
 temporary productions. Open to nationally established music professionals 
 and ensembles from Switzerland working in contemporary music\, music theat
 re\, sound art\, or contemporary folk music\, with prior Pro Helvetia supp
 ort. ELIGIBILITY: requires a connection to Switzerland (Swiss citizenship\
 , or permanent residency with regular artistic activity in Switzerland)\; 
 not open to practitioners without a Swiss connection. AMOUNT: maximum CHF 
 25\,000\, depending on overall project size. Deadlines twice a year: 1 Mar
 ch (23:59 CET) and 1 September (23:59 CEST). Apply via the Pro Helvetia po
 rtal.\n\nOrganisation: Pro Helvetia (Swiss Arts Council)\nLocation: Nation
 ally established Switzerland-based professionals and ensembles in contempo
 rary music\, music theatre\, sound art\, or contemporary folk.\nAward: Max
 imum CHF 25\,000 (depending on overall project size). No application fee.\
 nDuration: Creation/production of new works\; deadlines twice yearly (1 Ma
 rch and 1 September).\n\nMore: https://prohelvetia.ch/en/find-support/crea
 tion-and-production-contemporary-music?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantde
 sk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://prohelvetia.ch/en/find-support/creation-and-production-contempo
 rary-music?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Nationally established Switzerland-based professionals and ensembl
 es in contemporary music\, music theatre\, sound art\, or contemporary fol
 k.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:ctm-2027-radio-lab-in-listening@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260722T104007Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260906
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260907
SUMMARY:Deadline: CTM 2027 Radio Lab: In Listening (Berlin)
DESCRIPTION:CTM Festival's Radio Lab commissions new radio-based sound work
 s around the CTM 2027 theme In Listening\, premiered at the festival in Be
 rlin and broadcast on Deutschlandfunk Kultur. The previous cycle's commiss
 ion was EUR 5\,000 plus travel and lodging\; the 2027 fee is not restated 
 on the call page. Open worldwide. The same open-calls page also lists the 
 Resynthesising the Traditional 2027 artistic lab (same 6 September 2026 de
 adline) and Research Networking Day 2027 (deadline 25 October 2026). Radio
  Lab deadline 6 September 2026.\n\nOrganisation: CTM Festival with Deutsch
 landfunk Kultur\nLocation: Berlin\, Germany (CTM Festival\, 22-31 January 
 2027). Open worldwide.\nAward: Commission for a radio/sound work premiered
  at CTM 2027 and broadcast on Deutschlandfunk Kultur\; the previous cycle 
 offered EUR 5\,000 plus travel and lodging (2027 fee not restated on the c
 all page). No application fee.\nDuration: Work premiered at CTM Festival\,
  22-31 January 2027.\n\nMore: https://www.ctm-festival.de/festival-2027/op
 en-calls?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.ctm-festival.de/festival-2027/open-calls?utm_source=artific
 ialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Berlin\, Germany (CTM Festival\, 22-31 January 2027). Open worldwi
 de.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:statens-kunstnerstipend-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260722T104007Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260901
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260902
SUMMARY:Deadline: Statens kunstnerstipend: Norwegian State Artist Stipends 
 2026
DESCRIPTION:Norway's flagship state artist stipend and the largest individu
 al-artist commitment in the Nordic region\, with 1\,069 artists funded in 
 the most recent round. It is unrestricted support that buys working time r
 ather than funding a defined deliverable\, which suits research-heavy prac
 tices where the output is a system\, an instrument or a performance langua
 ge rather than a release. All artist groups are covered\, including music 
 and interdisciplinary practice. Note the deadline change: the application 
 form opens 1 August 2026 at 13:00\, and the funder has moved the closing d
 ate forward to 1 September\, stating on its own site that 'Soknadsfristen 
 for Statens kunstnerstipend flyttes frem til 1. september. Endringen gjeld
 er allerede fra 2026.' The move is intended to deliver decisions and payme
 nts earlier than in previous years. Applications go through a formal appli
 cation form on the Kulturdirektoratet site.\n\nOrganisation: Statens kunst
 nerstipend\, administered by Kulturdirektoratet (Arts and Culture Norway)\
 nLocation: Norway. For professionally active artists (yrkesaktive kunstnar
 ar) across all artist groups. Applications are assessed by 19 discipline-s
 pecific stipend committees\, which submit recommendations to a five-member
  selection board\; a sound or interdisciplinary artist should check which 
 committee fits their practice before applying\, as committee choice materi
 ally affects the reading.\nAward: NOK. Six stipend types\, from multi-year
  support of 1 to 10 years for artists at different career stages\, through
  to one-off grants (diversestipend) covering specific artistic expenses su
 ch as equipment\, travel and materials. Amounts are set per stipend type a
 nd published when the application form opens. No application fee\, no co-f
 inancing requirement.\nDuration: 1 to 10 years depending on stipend type\,
  plus one-off grants\n\nMore: https://www.kulturdirektoratet.no/statens-ku
 nstnerstipend?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.kulturdirektoratet.no/statens-kunstnerstipend?utm_source=ar
 tificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Norway. For professionally active artists (yrkesaktive kunstnarar)
  across all artist groups. Applications are assessed by 19 discipline-spec
 ific stipend committees\, which submit recommendations to a five-member se
 lection board\; a sound or interdisciplinary artist should check which com
 mittee fits their practice before applying\, as committee choice materiall
 y affects the reading.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:kulturdirektoratet-komposisjon-produksjon-2026@artificialnouveau.github
 .io
DTSTAMP:20260722T104007Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260915
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260916
SUMMARY:Deadline: Kulturdirektoratet: Komposisjon og produksjon av musikk (
 Autumn 2026)
DESCRIPTION:The strongest Norwegian fit for computer-based and live-coded m
 usic practice\, because the guidelines explicitly cover 'partitur- eller u
 toverbasert komposisjon' (score-based OR performer-based composition)\, co
 mposition on studio and digital platforms\, and collaborative creator proj
 ects. Performer-based composition is precisely the category live coding an
 d generative systems occupy\, so the practice does not have to be argued i
 nto the scheme sideways. All music styles qualify. Note the clean division
  of labour with Kulturdirektoratet's touring scheme: composition\, product
 ion\, recording and equipment belong here\, while concert and tour costs b
 elong in the turne scheme. Applications go through Kulturdirektoratet's on
 line portal. The funder states explicitly that it does not normally fund a
 ctivities completed before the deadline\, so the project must sit in the f
 uture at the point of applying. Deadline is 13:00 Norwegian time.\n\nOrgan
 isation: Kulturdirektoratet / Arts and Culture Norway (Kulturradet)\nLocat
 ion: Norway. Open to private individuals as well as private and public ins
 titutions\, organisations and other businesses. The scheme page states no 
 citizenship or residency requirement\, which makes this one of the more op
 en national schemes in the Nordic region. Applicants still in education ar
 e normally excluded.\nAward: NOK\, varies by project scale. Full funding i
 s available for composition honorariums\; other project elements are only 
 part-funded\, so structure the budget with the composition fee as the core
  ask and expect to co-finance the rest. Historical award levels are publis
 hed in Kulturdirektoratet's tildelingslister. No application fee.\nDuratio
 n: Per project\n\nMore: https://www.kulturdirektoratet.no/tilskuddsordning
 er/komposisjon-og-produksjon-av-musikk?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantde
 sk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.kulturdirektoratet.no/tilskuddsordninger/komposisjon-og-pro
 duksjon-av-musikk?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referra
 l
LOCATION:Norway. Open to private individuals as well as private and public 
 institutions\, organisations and other businesses. The scheme page states 
 no citizenship or residency requirement\, which makes this one of the more
  open national schemes in the Nordic region. Applicants still in education
  are normally excluded.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:koda-arbejdslegat-kunstmusik-2026-efterar@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260722T104007Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20261001
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20261002
SUMMARY:Deadline: Koda Kultur: Arbejdslegat\, Kunstmusikkens Genreomrade (A
 utumn 2026)
DESCRIPTION:The clearest structural fit in the Danish system for experiment
 al electronic and audiovisual practice. Koda defines the art-music genre a
 rea as covering 'audiovisuelle vaerker\, musikdramatik\, electronica\, spi
 l- og filmmusik\, lydkunst og improvisation'\, so audiovisual work\, elect
 ronica and sound art are named inside the fund's remit rather than sitting
  adjacent to it. The guidelines further say the applicant should work 'eks
 perimenterende og graensesogende med musik og lyd' (experimentally and at 
 the boundaries of music and sound). It funds a compositional work process 
 or artistic trajectory\, not commissioned works (those go to Vaerkskabelse
 spuljen) and not releases. Required materials are a one-page project descr
 iption as PDF\, a CV as PDF\, and one to three audio files (MP3 or MP4) do
 cumenting previous work. Applications go through Koda's online grant syste
 m. The funder states a decision within two months of the deadline. Closes 
 23:59.\n\nOrganisation: Koda Kultur\, administered with Dansk Komponistfor
 ening\nLocation: Denmark. The composer must be a member of Koda ('Komponis
 ten skal vaere medlem af Koda') and must apply personally under their own 
 CPR number. No separate nationality clause is stated\, but Koda membership
  plus a Danish CPR number is the binding requirement in practice.\nAward: 
 DKK 10\,000 to 40\,000 for smaller grants\; larger grants of DKK 50\,000 o
 r DKK 75\,000. No application fee\, no co-financing requirement.\nDuration
 : Compositional work process or artistic development period\n\nMore: https
 ://kultur.koda.dk/legatoversigt/arbejdslegat-kunstmusikkens-genreomraade/?
 utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://kultur.koda.dk/legatoversigt/arbejdslegat-kunstmusikkens-genreo
 mraade/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Denmark. The composer must be a member of Koda ('Komponisten skal 
 vaere medlem af Koda') and must apply personally under their own CPR numbe
 r. No separate nationality clause is stated\, but Koda membership plus a D
 anish CPR number is the binding requirement in practice.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:koda-vaerkskabelsespuljen-2026-efterar@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260722T104007Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20261001
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20261002
SUMMARY:Deadline: Koda Kultur: Vaerkskabelsespuljen\, New Work Creation (Au
 tumn 2026)
DESCRIPTION:Funds the development and production of new music and sound art
  works where a specific public performance is already envisaged\, which su
 its building a new audiovisual or live-electronic set for a named festival
  or venue slot. Eligible costs explicitly include equipment rental and doc
 umentation as well as composition fees and performer honorariums\, so hard
 ware hire and video capture of a performance are within scope\, which is u
 nusual among composition funds. You may apply either with a commission alr
 eady secured from another organisation or as the producer of your own work
 . It excludes general concert production costs (those belong to Koncertpro
 duktion og formidling) and publisher commissions\, and you cannot receive 
 support for the same project from more than one Koda Kultur pool at once. 
 Required materials are a one to two page project description as PDF\, a bu
 dget including a co-financing plan\, a CV\, a signed contract with the com
 missioning party where one exists\, and one to three representative audio 
 files. Three deadlines a year. Decision within two months. Closes 23:59.\n
 \nOrganisation: Koda Kultur\, with Dansk Komponistforening\nLocation: Denm
 ark. For composers and sound artists. Koda membership is not stated as an 
 explicit condition on this scheme page\, but it sits inside Koda Kultur's 
 art-music track and applications run through Koda's Danish-authenticated p
 ortal.\nAward: DKK. Covers composition fees\, performer honorariums\, equi
 pment rental and documentation. A co-financing plan is mandatory where the
  project budget exceeds DKK 30\,000. Grants up to DKK 30\,000 are paid imm
 ediately\; larger grants are paid 50 percent on approval and 50 percent on
  submission of final documentation. No application fee.\nDuration: Per wor
 k\, tied to a specific planned public performance\n\nMore: https://kultur.
 koda.dk/legatoversigt/vaerkskabelsepuljen/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugra
 ntdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://kultur.koda.dk/legatoversigt/vaerkskabelsepuljen/?utm_source=ar
 tificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Denmark. For composers and sound artists. Koda membership is not s
 tated as an explicit condition on this scheme page\, but it sits inside Ko
 da Kultur's art-music track and applications run through Koda's Danish-aut
 henticated portal.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:koda-koncertproduktion-formidling-2026-efterar@artificialnouveau.github
 .io
DTSTAMP:20260722T104007Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20261001
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20261002
SUMMARY:Deadline: Koda Kultur: Koncertproduktion og Formidling (Autumn 2026
 )
DESCRIPTION:Supports concert productions and dissemination work promoting n
 ew art music and sound art. The guidelines name 'elektroakustisk musik' di
 rectly among the eligible genre areas alongside acoustic chamber and orche
 stral music\, which is the clearest signal in the Koda system that electro
 nic and computer-based performance sits inside the fund's remit. The disse
 mination side is broad enough to cover podcasts\, journals and books about
  the work\, not only the concerts themselves. Applications require a budge
 t\, CVs of the relevant parties\, and audio files as MP3 or MP4 or video l
 inks. Three deadlines each year\, on 1 March\, 1 June and 1 October. A com
 mittee of five assesses applications and the funder states a decision appr
 oximately two months after the deadline. Final disbursement requires submi
 tted documentation and verification that Koda Kultur was credited. You can
 not hold support for the same project from more than one Koda Kultur pool.
 \n\nOrganisation: Koda Kultur\, with Dansk Komponistforening\nLocation: De
 nmark. Open to music professionals working in art music genres. Koda membe
 rship is not stated as a requirement on this scheme page. Both individuals
  and organisations may apply.\nAward: DKK\, amount not published on the sc
 heme page. As of 2026 the scheme pays lump sums rather than the previous d
 eficit-guarantee model. Eligible costs include venue rental\, musician fee
 s\, PR\, sound and lighting\, plus podcasts\, music journals and book publ
 ications on the dissemination side. No application fee.\nDuration: Per con
 cert production or dissemination initiative\n\nMore: https://kultur.koda.d
 k/legatoversigt/koncertproduktion-og-formidling/?utm_source=artificialnouv
 eaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://kultur.koda.dk/legatoversigt/koncertproduktion-og-formidling/?u
 tm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Denmark. Open to music professionals working in art music genres. 
 Koda membership is not stated as a requirement on this scheme page. Both i
 ndividuals and organisations may apply.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:koda-rejselegat-komponister-lydkunstnere-2026-efterar@artificialnouveau
 .github.io
DTSTAMP:20260722T104007Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20261001
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20261002
SUMMARY:Deadline: Koda Kultur: Rejselegat for Komponister og Lydkunstnere (
 Autumn 2026)
DESCRIPTION:Travel and accommodation support for documented trips tied to p
 remieres\, festival performances\, composer workshops\, study trips and re
 sidencies\, which maps directly onto international electronic and sound ar
 t festival bookings. Koda's art-music genre definition covers audiovisual 
 works\, electronica\, sound art and improvisation\, so the scheme is not l
 imited to notated concert music. Two features make it unusually practical:
  the climate-friendly travel supplement of DKK 650 per day makes overland 
 travel across Europe financially viable rather than a penalty\, and suppor
 t for accompanying personal assistants and children is explicitly provided
  for. This is reimbursement-style funding built from actual costs\, not a 
 lump sum. Applications are a maximum of one page via koda.onlinelegat.dk\,
  including a project description\, a budget or receipts\, a CV and an audi
 o sample. Three deadlines a year\, on 1 March\, 1 June and 1 October\, all
  23:59. Answer approximately two months after the deadline\, so apply well
  ahead of the trip.\n\nOrganisation: Koda Kultur\, with Dansk Komponistfor
 ening\nLocation: Denmark. Applicant must be a composer or sound artist who
  is a member of Koda\, working within art music genres. Individuals only\;
  groups cannot apply jointly.\nAward: DKK\, cost-based rather than a fixed
  sum. Cheapest public transport reimbursed\; car mileage at DKK 2.50/km wh
 ere driving is necessary\; accommodation up to DKK 1\,000 per night\; a DK
 K 650 per day supplement for climate-friendly travel\; DKK 1\,500 per pers
 onal assistant\, up to two\; DKK 1\,000 per accompanying child. Meals and 
 per diems are not covered. No application fee.\nDuration: Single trip\n\nM
 ore: https://kultur.koda.dk/legatoversigt/rejselegat-1/?utm_source=artific
 ialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://kultur.koda.dk/legatoversigt/rejselegat-1/?utm_source=artificia
 lnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Denmark. Applicant must be a composer or sound artist who is a mem
 ber of Koda\, working within art music genres. Individuals only\; groups c
 annot apply jointly.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:statens-kunstfond-bestillingsopgaver-musik-2026-efterar@artificialnouve
 au.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260722T104007Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20261001
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20261002
SUMMARY:Deadline: Statens Kunstfond: Bestillingsopgaver Musik\, Commission 
 Fees (Autumn 2026)
DESCRIPTION:Funds the composition fee for a new work when a creative artist
  has already received a commission from a third party. The key structural 
 point is that the composer applies\, not the commissioning body\, so an ar
 tist commissioned by a festival\, venue or ensemble is the correct applica
 nt. The scheme is open to all forms of music and explicitly names composer
 s\, songwriters\, sound artists\, arrangers and producers\, so an electron
 ic or audiovisual commission is not structurally excluded. Applications ar
 e submitted via Tilskudsportalen with MitID\; required attachments are the
  template document\, documentation of the commission agreement (an email s
 uffices)\, an MP3 audio sample\, and optionally a score of up to ten pages
 \, with a 25MB total attachment cap. The premiere or release of the new wo
 rk must take place after the application deadline\, so retroactive commiss
 ions are ineligible. Decisions issued within 12 weeks. Closes 14:00 Danish
  time.\n\nOrganisation: Statens Kunstfond / Danish Arts Foundation\, Proje
 ktstotteudvalget for Musik\nLocation: Denmark. No explicit nationality or 
 residency restriction in the guidelines\, but submission requires MitID au
 thentication via Tilskudsportalen\, which in practice means a Danish CPR o
 r CVR number is the real eligibility gate.\nAward: DKK\, no fixed ceiling 
 stated\; awards vary by project and available funds. Previous awards are l
 isted under tidligere tildelinger on kunst.dk. No application fee.\nDurati
 on: Single commissioned work\n\nMore: https://www.kunst.dk/for-ansoegere/s
 oeg-tilskud/bestillingsopgaver-musik?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk
 &utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.kunst.dk/for-ansoegere/soeg-tilskud/bestillingsopgaver-musi
 k?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Denmark. No explicit nationality or residency restriction in the g
 uidelines\, but submission requires MitID authentication via Tilskudsporta
 len\, which in practice means a Danish CPR or CVR number is the real eligi
 bility gate.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:konstnarsnamnden-internationellt-utbyte-musik-2026-host@artificialnouve
 au.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260722T104007Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20261022
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20261023
SUMMARY:Deadline: Konstnarsnamnden: Internationellt Utbyte och Resebidrag\,
  Musik (Autumn 2026)
DESCRIPTION:The Swedish Arts Grants Committee's international programme for
  music\, and the most usable Swedish route for an individual artist becaus
 e it does not require the company or organisation number that Kulturradet'
 s project grants demand. The grant works in both directions: it covers you
 r travel and accommodation for work abroad\, and it also covers a foreign 
 collaborator's travel and accommodation when you invite them to Sweden\, s
 ometimes including local rental costs\, which makes it a genuine tool for 
 building international collaborations rather than only for touring out. Ap
 plications go through Konstnarsnamnden's e-service\, with paper applicatio
 ns available as a fallback\, and require five to ten work samples as JPG\,
  MP3\, MP4 or MOV. An invitation letter from the foreign collaborator is m
 andatory where one exists. The autumn 2026 music round runs 28 August to 2
 2 October 2026 with decisions in December 2026. Digital applications accep
 ted until 14:00 on the final day. Retroactive awards are possible provided
  the application was submitted before the travel took place.\n\nOrganisati
 on: Konstnarsnamnden / Swedish Arts Grants Committee\nLocation: Sweden. Yo
 u must be resident in Sweden or practise your art predominantly in Sweden\
 , so this is a residency test rather than a citizenship test and foreign n
 ationals qualify if they meet it. You must be a professionally active arti
 st earning wholly or partly from artistic work\, not enrolled in studies e
 xceeding 50 percent at the time of decision\, have no state or municipal d
 ebts referred to Kronofogden and no bankruptcy\, and must not have receive
 d over EUR 300\,000 in de minimis aid over the previous three years.\nAwar
 d: SEK\, no fixed maximum\; minimum grant SEK 5\,000. Budget your actual t
 ravel and accommodation costs. Covers travel\, accommodation and in some c
 ases transport and participation fees. Does not cover production costs\, a
 rtist fees or wages. No application fee.\nDuration: Single exchange or tri
 p\n\nMore: https://www.konstnarsnamnden.se/internationella-program-och-res
 idens/konstnarsnamndens-internationella-program-for-musik/?utm_source=arti
 ficialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.konstnarsnamnden.se/internationella-program-och-residens/ko
 nstnarsnamndens-internationella-program-for-musik/?utm_source=artificialno
 uveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Sweden. You must be resident in Sweden or practise your art predom
 inantly in Sweden\, so this is a residency test rather than a citizenship 
 test and foreign nationals qualify if they meet it. You must be a professi
 onally active artist earning wholly or partly from artistic work\, not enr
 olled in studies exceeding 50 percent at the time of decision\, have no st
 ate or municipal debts referred to Kronofogden and no bankruptcy\, and mus
 t not have received over EUR 300\,000 in de minimis aid over the previous 
 three years.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:konstnarsnamnden-arbetsstipendium-musik-2026@artificialnouveau.github.i
 o
DTSTAMP:20260722T104007Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20261209
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20261210
SUMMARY:Deadline: Konstnarsnamnden: Arbets- och Langtidsstipendium\, Musik 
 (2026/27)
DESCRIPTION:Konstnarsnamnden's core unrestricted working stipend for music.
  It buys time rather than funding a defined deliverable\, which makes it w
 ell suited to research-heavy practice where the output is a system\, an in
 strument or a body of experimental work rather than a release or a concert
 . This is the Swedish functional equivalent of the Danish Arbejdslegater a
 nd the Norwegian Statens kunstnerstipend\, and an artist resident in Swede
 n should treat it as the primary annual target\, with the committee's inte
 rnational travel grant as a supplement. The application window is 9 Novemb
 er to 9 December 2026\, with decisions announced in March 2027\, so budget
  roughly a three-month decision lag. Applications go through the committee
 's e-service and must arrive by 14:00 on the final day. Note that the spec
 ific amount and the detailed music-discipline criteria are not published i
 n advance\; the individual scheme page goes live when the window opens\, s
 o confirm figures in early November 2026.\n\nOrganisation: Konstnarsnamnde
 n / Swedish Arts Grants Committee\nLocation: Sweden. Resident in Sweden or
  practising your art predominantly in Sweden\; professionally active and e
 arning wholly or partly from artistic work\; not enrolled in studies over 
 50 percent\; no debts referred to Kronofogden\; no bankruptcy.\nAward: SEK
 \, amount set by the committee and published when the application window o
 pens in November 2026. Work stipends (arbetsstipendium) run one to several
  years\; long-term stipends (langtidsstipendium) run considerably longer. 
 No application fee\, no co-financing requirement.\nDuration: Work stipend 
 of 1 or more years\, or long-term stipend\n\nMore: https://www.konstnarsna
 mnden.se/stipendier-och-bidrag/ansokningstider/?utm_source=artificialnouve
 augrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.konstnarsnamnden.se/stipendier-och-bidrag/ansokningstider/?
 utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Sweden. Resident in Sweden or practising your art predominantly in
  Sweden\; professionally active and earning wholly or partly from artistic
  work\; not enrolled in studies over 50 percent\; no debts referred to Kro
 nofogden\; no bankruptcy.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:statens-kunstfond-arbejdslegater-musik-2027@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260722T104007Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20270204
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20270205
SUMMARY:Deadline: Statens Kunstfond: Arbejdslegater for Musik (2027 Round)
DESCRIPTION:Denmark's principal work stipend for creative artists in music\
 , across all genres and explicitly including sound artists and producers a
 s well as notated composers\, which puts electronic and computer-based pra
 ctice inside the scheme on its face. The committee assesses 'kunstnerisk i
 ntention' (originality and a clear artistic vision) and 'handvaerk' (comma
 nd of one's musical tools)\, and states it values music that is challengin
 g\, thought-provoking\, innovative or artistically relevant\, so the appli
 cation should lead with the conceptual proposition rather than with output
  volume. Applications go through Tilskudsportalen with MitID\; mobile subm
 ission is not supported\, desktop only. Required attachments are the compl
 eted application template as PDF\, one to two MP3 audio examples\, and opt
 ionally up to ten pages of supplementary documentation. Groups may apply b
 ut each member must submit individually and document their own share of th
 e creative process. Decision within 12 weeks of the deadline\, notified by
  email and in Tilskudsportalen. Closes 14:00 Danish time.\n\nOrganisation:
  Statens Kunstfond / Danish Arts Foundation\, Projektstotteudvalget for Mu
 sik\nLocation: Denmark. Open to creative artists in music: composers\, son
 gwriters\, sound artists\, arrangers and producers. Applications are filed
  through Tilskudsportalen using MitID\, which in practice requires a Danis
 h CPR or CVR number\, so Danish registration is the real gate rather than 
 a stated nationality rule.\nAward: DKK. The committee sets the amount\; ap
 plicants do not request a sum. Both one-year and up to three-year stipends
  are awarded. No application fee\, no co-financing requirement. Past award
  levels are published at kunst.dk/tildelinger.\nDuration: Working stipend\
 , one-off or up to 3 years\n\nMore: https://www.kunst.dk/for-ansoegere/soe
 g-tilskud/arbejdslegater-for-musik?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&u
 tm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.kunst.dk/for-ansoegere/soeg-tilskud/arbejdslegater-for-musi
 k?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Denmark. Open to creative artists in music: composers\, songwriter
 s\, sound artists\, arrangers and producers. Applications are filed throug
 h Tilskudsportalen using MitID\, which in practice requires a Danish CPR o
 r CVR number\, so Danish registration is the real gate rather than a state
 d nationality rule.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:gema-stiftung-projektfoerderung-2026-oktober@artificialnouveau.github.i
 o
DTSTAMP:20260722T104007Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20261015
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20261016
SUMMARY:Deadline: GEMA-Stiftung: Projektfoerderung\, Project Funding (Octob
 er 2026 Deadline)
DESCRIPTION:The GEMA Foundation funds projects that stage works by several 
 living music authors\, which fits a curated multi-artist night\, a contemp
 orary or electronic music concert series or a festival programme far bette
 r than a solo project. It is not a classical-only fund\, but there is one 
 significant structural caveat: the foundation states that 'Nicht im Foerde
 rfokus stehen derzeit Projekte\, die sich ausschliesslich auf einzelne Mus
 ikautor:innen konzentrieren'\, meaning projects focused exclusively on a s
 ingle music author\, such as commissions\, portrait concerts or biographic
 al studies\, are currently outside its focus because of the volume of such
  applications. Applications must be in writing and must contain a detailed
  project description naming the participating composers or those in the pr
 ogramme plan\, plus a transparent budget showing any other funders. Two de
 adlines run each year\, 15 May and 15 October. The foundation warns explic
 itly that short-notice applications generally cannot be considered and tha
 t proposals should ideally arrive in the calendar year before the project 
 takes place\, so apply for a 2027 or 2028 event rather than something immi
 nent. Contact gemastiftung@gema.de.\n\nOrganisation: GEMA-Stiftung\nLocati
 on: Germany. No nationality or residency requirement is published\, but th
 e foundation states that 'Eine Voraussetzung fuer Foerdermassnahmen ist in
  der Regel die Mitgliedschaft der beteiligten Musikautoren und -verleger i
 n der GEMA'\, so as a rule the participating composers and publishers need
  GEMA membership. Both natural and legal persons may apply. Applications a
 re made in writing\, in German.\nAward: EUR\, no minimum or maximum publis
 hed. The foundation states it primarily wants to support projects that wou
 ld not be financeable without its grant\, possibly alongside selected othe
 r funders\, so a transparent budget naming all other funding sources is re
 quired. No application fee\, no fixed own-contribution percentage.\nDurati
 on: Project-based\; applications should be filed in the calendar year befo
 re the planned realisation\n\nMore: https://www.gemastiftung.de/de/foerder
 ung/antrag-projektfoerderung?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_med
 ium=referral
URL:https://www.gemastiftung.de/de/foerderung/antrag-projektfoerderung?utm_
 source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Germany. No nationality or residency requirement is published\, bu
 t the foundation states that 'Eine Voraussetzung fuer Foerdermassnahmen is
 t in der Regel die Mitgliedschaft der beteiligten Musikautoren und -verleg
 er in der GEMA'\, so as a rule the participating composers and publishers 
 need GEMA membership. Both natural and legal persons may apply. Applicatio
 ns are made in writing\, in German.
END:VEVENT
END:VCALENDAR
